# GDScript Patterns

## Services Before Custom Logic

Check `scripts/autoloads/` before writing scene-local logic. If a behaviour recurs — interaction, dialogue, economy queries, contract checks — it belongs in a system, not a scene.

Autoloads are the source of truth for game state:
- `GameState` — time, money, reputation
- `Economy` — port prices, supply/demand
- `ContractBoard` — contracts, deadlines, consequences
- `FleetManager` — ships, captains, routes
- `World` — port and island registry

## Jigsaw Components

Scenes expose signals and `@export` slots. They do not reach outside themselves.

```gdscript
# BAD
get_parent().get_parent().get_node("HUD").show_prompt(text)

# GOOD
InteractionSystem.show_prompt(text)
# or
signal interaction_triggered(context)
```

## Data in Resources

Port data, cargo types, contract templates → `resources/data/` as `.tres` Resource subclasses. Never hardcode game data in scripts.

```gdscript
# BAD
var exports = ["Fish", "Salt"]

# GOOD
@export var port_data: PortData
var exports = port_data.exports
```

## Generic First

Build the reusable system before the specific instance. `DialogueRunner` before the dock NPC. The scrollable list before the contract board. No one-offs that get refactored later.
